Tuesday September 3rd 2013 11:06 am -04:00,Well the variables used in the calling function are called arguments whereas the variables used in the function definition are called parameters in python language.										 For example if you have this function:  >>def explain_param_vs_arg(param1 param2):    print(param1 param2)   and call it like this:     >>explain_param_vs_arg(arg1 arg2)    The variables param1 and param2 are the parameters and the values that you give them in this case arg1 and arg2 are the arguments., Resolved,2
